  platonic (eternal forms vs impermanence)
]

## Notes
# Implementation notes, edge cases, open questions

### Extraction Limitations
This library was extracted from experiments 008 and 010 only. The roadmap referenced
experiments 004 and 006 which were not found in the codebase. This extraction may be
incomplete and should be expanded when/if those experiments are located.

### Vocabulary Gaps
The following Buddhist terms are mentioned in NEXT.md but not fully defined in available experiments:
- san (sangha?) - not found in experiments
- bod (bodhi/awakening) - mentioned but not elaborated
- duk (dukkha) - "suf" (suffering) is used instead

### Semantic Coherence
Experiment 010 shows exceptional semantic coherence (99.8%) for Buddhist phrases using
the Limn-native embedder, suggesting that:
1. Buddhist vocabulary was well-represented in training corpus (experiments 004-006)
2. Buddhist compositional patterns are well-captured by the embedder
3. The pattern extraction methodology is sound

### Implementation Questions
